{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Fifty years ago, when I began exploring the ocean,"},{"time":3000,"text":"no one -- not Jacques Perrin, not Jacques Cousteau or Rachel Carson --"},{"time":9000,"text":"imagined that we could do anything to harm the ocean"},{"time":12000,"text":"by what we put into it or by what we took out of it."},{"time":15000,"text":"It seemed, at that time, to be a sea of Eden,"},{"time":18000,"text":"but now we know, and now we are facing paradise lost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24000,"text":"I want to share with you"},{"time":27000,"text":"my personal view of changes in the sea that affect all of us,"},{"time":30000,"text":"and to consider why it matters that in 50 years, we've lost --"},{"time":34000,"text":"actually, we've taken, we've eaten --"},{"time":37000,"text":"more than 90 percent of the big fish in the sea;"},{"time":40000,"text":"why you should care that nearly half of the coral reefs have disappeared;"},{"time":44000,"text":"why a mysterious depletion of oxygen in large areas of the Pacific"},{"time":50000,"text":"should concern not only the creatures that are dying,"},{"time":53000,"text":"but it really should concern you."},{"time":56000,"text":"It does concern you, as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58000,"text":"I'm haunted by the thought of what Ray Anderson calls \"tomorrow's child,\""},{"time":63000,"text":"asking why we didn't do something on our watch"},{"time":67000,"text":"to save sharks and bluefin tuna and squids and coral reefs and the living ocean"},{"time":72000,"text":"while there still was time."},{"time":74000,"text":"Well, now is that time."},{"time":77000,"text":"I hope for your help"},{"time":80000,"text":"to explore and protect the wild ocean"},{"time":83000,"text":"in ways that will restore the health and,"},{"time":86000,"text":"in so doing, secure hope for humankind."},{"time":90000,"text":"Health to the ocean means health for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"And I hope Jill Tarter's wish to engage Earthlings includes dolphins and whales"},{"time":100000,"text":"and other sea creatures"},{"time":102000,"text":"in this quest to find intelligent life elsewhere in the universe."},{"time":105000,"text":"And I hope, Jill, that someday"},{"time":108000,"text":"we will find evidence that there is intelligent life among humans on this planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117000,"text":"Did I say that? I guess I did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"For me, as a scientist,"},{"time":125000,"text":"it all began in 1953"},{"time":128000,"text":"when I first tried scuba."},{"time":131000,"text":"It's when I first got to know fish swimming"},{"time":134000,"text":"in something other than lemon slices and butter."},{"time":137000,"text":"I actually love diving at night;"},{"time":140000,"text":"you see a lot of fish then that you don't see in the daytime."},{"time":143000,"text":"Diving day and night was really easy for me in 1970,"},{"time":147000,"text":"when I led a team of aquanauts living underwater for weeks at a time --"},{"time":152000,"text":"at the same time that astronauts were putting their footprints on the moon."},{"time":159000,"text":"In 1979 I had a chance to put my footprints on the ocean floor"},{"time":163000,"text":"while using this personal submersible called Jim."},{"time":166000,"text":"It was six miles offshore and 1,250 feet down."},{"time":170000,"text":"It's one of my favorite bathing suits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175000,"text":"Since then, I've used about 30 kinds of submarines"},{"time":179000,"text":"and I've started three companies and a nonprofit foundation called Deep Search"},{"time":182000,"text":"to design and build systems"},{"time":185000,"text":"to access the deep sea."},{"time":187000,"text":"I led a five-year National Geographic expedition,"},{"time":190000,"text":"the Sustainable Seas expeditions,"},{"time":193000,"text":"using these little subs."},{"time":195000,"text":"They're so simple to drive that even a scientist can do it."},{"time":198000,"text":"And I'm living proof."},{"time":200000,"text":"Astronauts and aquanauts alike"},{"time":202000,"text":"really appreciate the importance of air, food, water, temperature --"},{"time":207000,"text":"all the things you need to stay alive in space or under the sea."},{"time":211000,"text":"I heard astronaut Joe Allen explain"},{"time":214000,"text":"how he had to learn everything he could about his life support system"},{"time":217000,"text":"and then do everything he could"},{"time":220000,"text":"to take care of his life support system;"},{"time":223000,"text":"and then he pointed to this and he said, \"Life support system.\""},{"time":228000,"text":"We need to learn everything we can about it"},{"time":231000,"text":"and do everything we can to take care of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"The poet Auden said, \"Thousands have lived without love;"},{"time":238000,"text":"none without water.\""},{"time":241000,"text":"Ninety-seven percent of Earth's water is ocean."},{"time":244000,"text":"No blue, no green."},{"time":247000,"text":"If you think the ocean isn't important,"},{"time":249000,"text":"imagine Earth without it."},{"time":252000,"text":"Mars comes to mind."},{"time":254000,"text":"No ocean, no life support system."},{"time":256000,"text":"I gave a talk not so long ago at the World Bank"},{"time":259000,"text":"and I showed this amazing image of Earth"},{"time":262000,"text":"and I said, \"There it is! The World Bank!\""},{"time":265000,"text":"That's where all the assets are!"},{"time":271000,"text":"And we've been trawling them down"},{"time":274000,"text":"much faster than the natural systems can replenish them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"Tim Worth says the economy is a wholly-owned subsidiary of the environment."},{"time":280000,"text":"With every drop of water you drink,"},{"time":282000,"text":"every breath you take,"},{"time":284000,"text":"you're connected to the sea."},{"time":287000,"text":"No matter where on Earth you live."},{"time":289000,"text":"Most of the oxygen in the atmosphere is generated by the sea."},{"time":292000,"text":"Over time, most of the planet's organic carbon"},{"time":295000,"text":"has been absorbed and stored there,"},{"time":298000,"text":"mostly by microbes."},{"time":300000,"text":"The ocean drives climate and weather,"},{"time":302000,"text":"stabilizes temperature, shapes Earth's chemistry."},{"time":304000,"text":"Water from the sea forms clouds"},{"time":306000,"text":"that return to the land and the seas"},{"time":309000,"text":"as rain, sleet and snow,"},{"time":311000,"text":"and provides home for about 97 percent of life in the world,"},{"time":315000,"text":"maybe in the universe."},{"time":317000,"text":"No water, no life;"},{"time":319000,"text":"no blue, no green."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"Yet we have this idea, we humans,"},{"time":324000,"text":"that the Earth -- all of it: the oceans, the skies --"},{"time":327000,"text":"are so vast and so resilient"},{"time":330000,"text":"it doesn't matter what we do to it."},{"time":332000,"text":"That may have been true 10,000 years ago,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and maybe even 1,000 years ago"},{"time":338000,"text":"but in the last 100, especially in the last 50,"},{"time":340000,"text":"we've drawn down the assets,"},{"time":342000,"text":"the air, the water, the wildlife"},{"time":345000,"text":"that make our lives possible."},{"time":348000,"text":"New technologies are helping us to understand"},{"time":351000,"text":"the nature of nature;"},{"time":354000,"text":"the nature of what's happening,"},{"time":356000,"text":"showing us our impact on the Earth."},{"time":359000,"text":"I mean, first you have to know that you've got a problem."},{"time":362000,"text":"And fortunately, in our time,"},{"time":365000,"text":"we've learned more about the problems than in all preceding history."},{"time":368000,"text":"And with knowing comes caring."},{"time":371000,"text":"And with caring, there's hope"},{"time":373000,"text":"that we can find an enduring place for ourselves"},{"time":376000,"text":"within the natural systems that support us."},{"time":379000,"text":"But first we have to know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"Three years ago, I met John Hanke,"},{"time":385000,"text":"who's the head of Google Earth,"},{"time":387000,"text":"and I told him how much I loved being able to hold the world in my hands"},{"time":390000,"text":"and go exploring vicariously."},{"time":392000,"text":"But I asked him: \"When are you going to finish it?"},{"time":395000,"text":"You did a great job with the land, the dirt."},{"time":398000,"text":"What about the water?\""},{"time":401000,"text":"Since then, I've had the great pleasure of working with the Googlers,"},{"time":405000,"text":"with DOER Marine, with National Geographic,"},{"time":408000,"text":"with dozens of the best institutions and scientists around the world,"},{"time":413000,"text":"ones that we could enlist,"},{"time":416000,"text":"to put the ocean in Google Earth."},{"time":419000,"text":"And as of just this week, last Monday,"},{"time":421000,"text":"Google Earth is now whole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"Consider this: Starting right here at the convention center,"},{"time":427000,"text":"we can find the nearby aquarium,"},{"time":429000,"text":"we can look at where we're sitting,"},{"time":431000,"text":"and then we can cruise up the coast to the big aquarium, the ocean,"},{"time":434000,"text":"and California's four national marine sanctuaries,"},{"time":437000,"text":"and the new network of state marine reserves"},{"time":440000,"text":"that are beginning to protect and restore some of the assets"},{"time":444000,"text":"We can flit over to Hawaii"},{"time":447000,"text":"and see the real Hawaiian Islands:"},{"time":450000,"text":"not just the little bit that pokes through the surface,"},{"time":453000,"text":"but also what's below."},{"time":456000,"text":"To see -- wait a minute, we can go kshhplash! --"},{"time":459000,"text":"right there, ha --"},{"time":462000,"text":"under the ocean, see what the whales see."},{"time":465000,"text":"We can go explore the other side of the Hawaiian Islands."},{"time":470000,"text":"We can go actually and swim around on Google Earth"},{"time":474000,"text":"and visit with humpback whales."},{"time":478000,"text":"These are the gentle giants that I've had the pleasure of meeting face to face"},{"time":483000,"text":"many times underwater."},{"time":486000,"text":"There's nothing quite like being personally inspected by a whale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"We can pick up and fly to the deepest place:"},{"time":493000,"text":"seven miles down, the Mariana Trench,"},{"time":496000,"text":"where only two people have ever been."},{"time":498000,"text":"Imagine that. It's only seven miles,"},{"time":501000,"text":"but only two people have been there, 49 years ago."},{"time":504000,"text":"One-way trips are easy."},{"time":507000,"text":"We need new deep-diving submarines."},{"time":510000,"text":"How about some X Prizes for ocean exploration?"},{"time":513000,"text":"We need to see deep trenches, the undersea mountains,"},{"time":517000,"text":"and understand life in the deep sea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"We can now go to the Arctic."},{"time":523000,"text":"Just ten years ago I stood on the ice at the North Pole."},{"time":527000,"text":"An ice-free Arctic Ocean may happen in this century."},{"time":532000,"text":"That's bad news for the polar bears."},{"time":536000,"text":"That's bad news for us too."},{"time":539000,"text":"Excess carbon dioxide is not only driving global warming,"},{"time":542000,"text":"it's also changing ocean chemistry,"},{"time":545000,"text":"making the sea more acidic."},{"time":548000,"text":"That's bad news for coral reefs and oxygen-producing plankton."},{"time":551000,"text":"Also it's bad news for us."},{"time":554000,"text":"We're putting hundreds of millions of tons of plastic"},{"time":557000,"text":"and other trash into the sea."},{"time":559000,"text":"Millions of tons of discarded fishing nets,"},{"time":562000,"text":"gear that continues to kill."},{"time":565000,"text":"We're clogging the ocean, poisoning the planet's circulatory system,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and we're taking out hundreds of millions of tons of wildlife,"},{"time":572000,"text":"all carbon-based units."},{"time":577000,"text":"Barbarically, we're killing sharks for shark fin soup,"},{"time":582000,"text":"undermining food chains that shape planetary chemistry"},{"time":585000,"text":"and drive the carbon cycle, the nitrogen cycle,"},{"time":588000,"text":"the oxygen cycle, the water cycle --"},{"time":591000,"text":"our life support system."},{"time":594000,"text":"We're still killing bluefin tuna; truly endangered"},{"time":598000,"text":"and much more valuable alive than dead."},{"time":602000,"text":"All of these parts are part of our life support system."},{"time":607000,"text":"We kill using long lines, with baited hooks every few feet"},{"time":613000,"text":"that may stretch for 50 miles or more."},{"time":615000,"text":"Industrial trawlers and draggers are scraping the sea floor"},{"time":619000,"text":"like bulldozers, taking everything in their path."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"Using Google Earth you can witness trawlers --"},{"time":625000,"text":"in China, the North Sea, the Gulf of Mexico --"},{"time":629000,"text":"shaking the foundation of our life support system,"},{"time":633000,"text":"leaving plumes of death in their path."},{"time":635000,"text":"The next time you dine on sushi -- or sashimi,"},{"time":638000,"text":"or swordfish steak, or shrimp cocktail,"},{"time":640000,"text":"whatever wildlife you happen to enjoy from the ocean --"},{"time":643000,"text":"think of the real cost."},{"time":646000,"text":"For every pound that goes to market,"},{"time":648000,"text":"more than 10 pounds, even 100 pounds,"},{"time":652000,"text":"may be thrown away as bycatch."},{"time":656000,"text":"This is the consequence of not knowing"},{"time":659000,"text":"that there are limits to what we can take out of the sea."},{"time":662000,"text":"This chart shows the decline in ocean wildlife"},{"time":666000,"text":"from 1900 to 2000."},{"time":669000,"text":"The highest concentrations are in red."},{"time":672000,"text":"In my lifetime, imagine,"},{"time":674000,"text":"90 percent of the big fish have been killed."},{"time":678000,"text":"Most of the turtles, sharks, tunas and whales"},{"time":680000,"text":"are way down in numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"But, there is good news."},{"time":686000,"text":"Ten percent of the big fish still remain."},{"time":688000,"text":"There are still some blue whales."},{"time":690000,"text":"There are still some krill in Antarctica."},{"time":693000,"text":"There are a few oysters in Chesapeake Bay."},{"time":695000,"text":"Half the coral reefs are still in pretty good shape,"},{"time":698000,"text":"a jeweled belt around the middle of the planet."},{"time":701000,"text":"There's still time, but not a lot,"},{"time":704000,"text":"to turn things around."},{"time":706000,"text":"But business as usual means that in 50 years,"},{"time":708000,"text":"there may be no coral reefs --"},{"time":711000,"text":"and no commercial fishing, because the fish will simply be gone."},{"time":715000,"text":"Imagine the ocean without fish."},{"time":719000,"text":"Imagine what that means to our life support system."},{"time":723000,"text":"Natural systems on the land are in big trouble too,"},{"time":726000,"text":"but the problems are more obvious,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and some actions are being taken to protect trees, watersheds and wildlife."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"And in 1872, with Yellowstone National Park,"},{"time":738000,"text":"the United States began establishing a system of parks"},{"time":741000,"text":"that some say was the best idea America ever had."},{"time":746000,"text":"About 12 percent of the land around the world is now protected:"},{"time":750000,"text":"safeguarding biodiversity, providing a carbon sink,"},{"time":754000,"text":"generating oxygen, protecting watersheds."},{"time":756000,"text":"And, in 1972, this nation began to establish a counterpart in the sea,"},{"time":761000,"text":"National Marine Sanctuaries."},{"time":763000,"text":"That's another great idea."},{"time":765000,"text":"The good news is"},{"time":767000,"text":"that there are now more than 4,000 places in the sea, around the world,"},{"time":771000,"text":"that have some kind of protection."},{"time":773000,"text":"And you can find them on Google Earth."},{"time":775000,"text":"The bad news is"},{"time":777000,"text":"that you have to look hard to find them."},{"time":779000,"text":"In the last three years, for example,"},{"time":781000,"text":"the U.S. protected 340,000 square miles of ocean as national monuments."},{"time":787000,"text":"But it only increased from 0.6 of one percent"},{"time":790000,"text":"to 0.8 of one percent of the ocean protected, globally."},{"time":795000,"text":"Protected areas do rebound,"},{"time":798000,"text":"but it takes a long time to restore"},{"time":800000,"text":"50-year-old rockfish or monkfish, sharks or sea bass,"},{"time":804000,"text":"or 200-year-old orange roughy."},{"time":806000,"text":"We don't consume 200-year-old cows or chickens."},{"time":810000,"text":"Protected areas provide hope"},{"time":813000,"text":"that the creatures of Ed Wilson's dream"},{"time":816000,"text":"of an encyclopedia of life, or the census of marine life,"},{"time":820000,"text":"will live not just as a list,"},{"time":824000,"text":"a photograph, or a paragraph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"With scientists around the world, I've been looking at the 99 percent of the ocean"},{"time":831000,"text":"that is open to fishing -- and mining, and drilling, and dumping, and whatever --"},{"time":835000,"text":"to search out hope spots,"},{"time":837000,"text":"and try to find ways to give them and us a secure future."},{"time":841000,"text":"Such as the Arctic --"},{"time":843000,"text":"we have one chance, right now, to get it right."},{"time":846000,"text":"Or the Antarctic, where the continent is protected,"},{"time":849000,"text":"but the surrounding ocean is being stripped of its krill, whales and fish."},{"time":855000,"text":"Sargasso Sea's three million square miles of floating forest"},{"time":860000,"text":"is being gathered up to feed cows."},{"time":863000,"text":"97 percent of the land in the Galapagos Islands is protected,"},{"time":867000,"text":"but the adjacent sea is being ravaged by fishing."},{"time":871000,"text":"It's true too in Argentina"},{"time":873000,"text":"on the Patagonian shelf, which is now in serious trouble."},{"time":876000,"text":"The high seas, where whales, tuna and dolphins travel --"},{"time":881000,"text":"the largest, least protected, ecosystem on Earth,"},{"time":884000,"text":"filled with luminous creatures,"},{"time":887000,"text":"living in dark waters that average two miles deep."},{"time":890000,"text":"They flash, and sparkle, and glow"},{"time":893000,"text":"with their own living light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896000,"text":"There are still places in the sea as pristine as I knew as a child."},{"time":899000,"text":"The next 10 years may be the most important,"},{"time":903000,"text":"and the next 10,000 years the best chance our species will have"},{"time":907000,"text":"to protect what remains of the natural systems that give us life."},{"time":913000,"text":"To cope with climate change, we need new ways to generate power."},{"time":916000,"text":"We need new ways, better ways, to cope with poverty, wars and disease."},{"time":922000,"text":"We need many things to keep and maintain the world as a better place."},{"time":926000,"text":"But, nothing else will matter"},{"time":929000,"text":"if we fail to protect the ocean."},{"time":932000,"text":"Our fate and the ocean's are one."},{"time":936000,"text":"We need to do for the ocean what Al Gore did for the skies above."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940000,"text":"A global plan of action"},{"time":943000,"text":"with a world conservation union, the IUCN,"},{"time":945000,"text":"is underway to protect biodiversity,"},{"time":947000,"text":"to mitigate and recover from the impacts of climate change,"},{"time":951000,"text":"on the high seas and in coastal areas,"},{"time":955000,"text":"wherever we can identify critical places."},{"time":959000,"text":"New technologies are needed to map, photograph and explore"},{"time":963000,"text":"the 95 percent of the ocean that we have yet to see."},{"time":967000,"text":"The goal is to protect biodiversity,"},{"time":970000,"text":"to provide stability and resilience."},{"time":972000,"text":"We need deep-diving subs,"},{"time":974000,"text":"new technologies to explore the ocean."},{"time":977000,"text":"We need, maybe, an expedition --"},{"time":980000,"text":"a TED at sea --"},{"time":982000,"text":"that could help figure out the next steps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"And so, I suppose you want to know what my wish is."},{"time":989000,"text":"I wish you would use all means at your disposal --"},{"time":994000,"text":"films, expeditions, the web, new submarines --"},{"time":997000,"text":"and campaign to ignite public support"},{"time":1000000,"text":"for a global network of marine protected areas --"},{"time":1003000,"text":"hope spots large enough to save and restore the ocean,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"the blue heart of the planet."},{"time":1010000,"text":"How much?"},{"time":1012000,"text":"Some say 10 percent, some say 30 percent."},{"time":1015000,"text":"You decide: how much of your heart do you want to protect?"},{"time":1020000,"text":"Whatever it is,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"a fraction of one percent is not enough."},{"time":1026000,"text":"My wish is a big wish,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"but if we can make it happen, it can truly change the world,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"and help ensure the survival"},{"time":1035000,"text":"of what actually -- as it turns out -- is my favorite species;"},{"time":1041000,"text":"that would be us."},{"time":1043000,"text":"For the children of today,"},{"time":1045000,"text":"for tomorrow's child:"},{"time":1047000,"text":"as never again, now is the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}